column5: This is my home land and in the 4th pic to the top right is where me late uncle wallace and aunt helen lived.  This made me home sick aswell.    The one rock beach shot,we use to scoop up Kaplin with our hands.That be like  smelts to yous here.

That was great Brian (Full volume) thanks for putting it up.  I've been fortunate to have sailed along the beautiful east & north coasts of Newfoundland a few times, close enuff to see it well, and even dodged the many iceburgs, but never had the pleasure of actually visiting the island.....but maybe some day if I'm really lucky !!!!
Tanks me Brudder. Dat's the nicest ting I seen and heard all week fer shore!
Yep Harry could sing a tone and make ya sit back and remember when. Lew you are a very fortunate man to be able to see alot of things many only dream of. BTW TY.

Here's one of my most favourite Newfie jokes.  There was a concert happening in town.  And the singer paused part way through his song... He claps once...and says "for every clap I make, one child dies from hunger". He claps again, and again, and again Well this is just too much for one of the locals who stands up and shouts... "well for Jesus H Christ laddy, stop yer focking clapping"  lol I think I got it right.
I hates when they claps their focking hands and they kill de kids of hunger!!!
